				strong ''
					StaticText 'README.md'
			heading 'NAME'
			paragraph ''
				StaticText 'autojump - a faster way to navigate your filesystem'
			heading 'DESCRIPTION'
			paragraph ''
				StaticText 'autojump is a faster way to navigate your filesystem. It works by maintaining a database of the directories you use the most from the command line.'
			paragraph ''
				emphasis ''
					StaticText 'Directories must be visited first before they can be jumped to.'
			heading 'USAGE'
			paragraph ''
				code ''
					StaticText 'j'
				StaticText 'is a convenience wrapper function around'
				code ''
					StaticText 'autojump'
				StaticText '. Any option that can be used with'
				code ''
					StaticText 'autojump'
				StaticText 'can be used with'
				code ''
					StaticText 'j'
				StaticText 'and vice versa.'
			list ''
				listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Jump To A Directory That Contains'

						StaticText ':'
					code ''
						StaticText 'j foo'
					button ''
						image ''
				listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Jump To A Child Directory:'
					paragraph ''
						StaticText "Sometimes it's convenient to jump to a child directory (sub-directory of current directory) rather than typing out the full name."
					code ''
						StaticText 'jc bar'
					button ''
						image ''
				listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Open File Manager To Directories (instead of jumping):'
					paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Instead of jumping to a directory, you can open a file explorer window (Mac Finder, Windows Explorer, GNOME Nautilus, etc.) to the directory instead.'
					code ''
						StaticText 'jo music'
					button ''
						image ''
					paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Opening a file manager to a child directory is also supported:'
					code ''

					button ''
						image ''
				listitem ''
					ListMarker '•'
					paragraph ''
						StaticText 'Using Multiple Arguments:'
					paragraph ''

					code ''
						StaticText '30   /home/user/mail/inbox'
						StaticText ''
						StaticText '10   /home/user/work/inbox'
					button ''
						image ''
					paragraph ''
						code ''
							StaticText 'j in'
						StaticText 'would jump into /home/user/mail/inbox as the higher weighted entry. However you can pass multiple arguments to autojump to prefer a different entry. In the above example,'
						code ''
							StaticText 'j w in'
						StaticText 'would then change directory to /home/user/work/inbox.'
